text: Internet is limited to 3 Mbps per host
Sony Playstation 2 is allowed by the University firewall
Guests' network is rate-limited to 5 Mb/s per user
P2P application is separately capped at 30 Mbps for the entire campus
Currently, the University of Illinois does not have any rate limits set in place
SMTP is allowed by the University firewall
ACT/IT Infrastructure monitors traffic on the network for the purpose of maintaining proper network function
The ResNet cap is currently 200 gigabytes per each 7 day period of combined incoming and outgoing traffic
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
Students have a quota of 5 GB per day The quota is reset at 6am
FTP and SFTP servers are allowed by the University firewall
RHIT-OPEN will work in labs, classrooms and residence halls but does not allow the user to access the internal Rose-Hulman network
